---
description: Enforce Comm for server-client communication
alwaysApply: true
---

# Server Communication Uses Comm

Use `sleitnick/comm` as the default and required approach for new server-client communication.

For new networking code, do not directly create or manage `RemoteEvent`, `RemoteFunction`, `UnreliableRemoteEvent`, or ad-hoc remote folders.

Allowed exceptions:
- Existing legacy networking that is not currently being refactored.
- Roblox APIs that are not server-client remotes (for example `MessagingService`).
- Explicit user instruction to use a non-Comm pattern.

## Prefer

```luau
local ReplicatedStorage: ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")

local Packages: Folder = ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild("Packages") :: Folder
local Comm: any = require(Packages:WaitForChild("Comm"))

local remotesFolder: Folder = ReplicatedStorage:WaitForChild("Remotes") :: Folder
local serverComm: any = Comm.ServerComm.new(remotesFolder, "ToolProvider")
local grantToolSignal: any = serverComm:CreateSignal("GrantTool")
```

## Avoid

```luau
local ReplicatedStorage: ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")

local remotesFolder: Folder = Instance.new("Folder")
remotesFolder.Name = "Remotes"
remotesFolder.Parent = ReplicatedStorage

local grantToolRemote: RemoteEvent = Instance.new("RemoteEvent")
grantToolRemote.Name = "GrantTool"
grantToolRemote.Parent = remotesFolder
```
